{"to":["lisa.caregiver@example.com"],"subject":"Welcome & Key Insights for Supporting Ethan","body":"Hi Lisa,

Thank you for taking the time to get to know Ethan. I wanted to share a few key points that will help you feel prepared during your first days with him.

Daily rhythm
• Ethan thrives on predictability. He typically wakes around 7:00 a.m., enjoys breakfast (oatmeal topped with banana is a favorite), and then does some gentle stretching or light exercises.
• From 10:00–11:00 a.m. he likes to work on puzzles – they keep him calm and focused.
• Lunch is about 12:30 p.m.; simple, warm sandwiches go over well.
• Early afternoon (1:00–2:30 p.m.) is a good window for quiet reading time or listening to soft music.
• He has a therapy appointment most days at 3:00 p.m., so a calm transition beforehand helps.
• Dinner is at 6:00 p.m., followed by a nature show, and bedtime starts at 8:30 p.m.

Food preferences
• Prefers foods served warm and smooth textures.
• Favors snacks such as apple slices with peanut butter or crackers with cheese.
• A quiet, low-noise setting at meals helps him eat comfortably.

Interests & activities
• He loves animals and enjoys simple trips to a zoo or farm.
• Water play and beginner swimming sessions are exciting for him.
• Creative outlets – drawing or painting – are great rainy-day options.
• Puzzles are both soothing and engaging.

Sensory & communication notes
• Sudden loud noises can be overwhelming; giving him a heads-up or finding a quieter space makes a big difference.
• He is learning to tell us when he needs a break; offering that option before frustration builds is helpful.

Please feel free to reach out with any questions as you settle in. I’m always happy to talk through what works (or doesn’t) for Ethan.

Looking forward to working together!

Best,
Jane","cc":null,"bcc":null,"execution_log_path":"data/logs/item43_execution_log.json"}
